Install Java & Eclipse (repeat steps 1–2 from Expt 1).

Download Selenium JARs & ChromeDriver (repeat steps 3–4 from Expt 1; copy to new folders).

Create Eclipse Project

Name: Expt4_Registration.

Create libs/ and drivers/ folders as above.

Add all Selenium JARs to build path; put chromedriver.exe in drivers/.

Write the Registration-test Code

Package: expt4. Class: AmazonUserRegistrationTest.

Paste:

java
Copy
Edit
package expt4;

import org.openqa.selenium.By;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.chrome.ChromeDriver;

public class AmazonUserRegistrationTest {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.setProperty("webdriver.chrome.driver",
        "drivers/chromedriver.exe");
    WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();
    driver.get("https://www.amazon.com/");

    // Click “Hello, Sign in”
    driver.findElement(By.id("nav-signin-tooltip")).click();
    // Click “Create your Amazon account”
    driver.findElement(By.id("createAccountSubmit")).click();

    // Capture and verify heading
    String heading = driver.findElement(By.tagName("h1")).getText();
    System.out.println("Heading: " + heading);
    if (heading.toLowerCase().contains("create account")) {
      System.out.println("✅ Registration page reached");
    } else {
      System.out.println("❌ Failed to reach registration");
    }
    driver.quit();
  }
}
Run & Show

Run as Java Application.

Examiner sees browser clicks, then console:

